				<article id="post-409" class="post-409 project type-project status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry project_category-citythatworks et_pb_post">

				
					<div class="entry-content">
					<div id="et-boc" class="et-boc">
			
			<div class="et_builder_inner_content et_pb_gutters3">
				<div class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_0 et_pb_fullwidth_section et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
					<section class="et_pb_module et_pb_fullwidth_header et_pb_fullwidth_header_0 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_container center">
					<div class="header-content-container center">
					<div class="header-content">
						
						<h1 class="et_pb_module_header">Building for Chicago's People</h1>
						<span class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_subhead">The City That Works</span>
						<div class="et_pb_header_content_wrapper"></div>
						
					</div>
				</div>
					
				</div>
				<div class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_overlay"></div>
				<div class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_scroll"></div>
			</section>
				
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_section --><div class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_1 et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
					<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_0">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4 et_pb_column_0    et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_0 et_pb_bg_layout_light  et_pb_text_align_left">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner">
					<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="#alltopics">View all topics for &#8220;The City That Works&#8221; &gt;</a></p>
				</div>
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_text --><div class="et_pb_module et_pb_slider et_pb_slider_0 et_pb_slider_fullwidth_off">
				<div class="et_pb_slides">
					<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_0 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center et-pb-active-slide">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">1 of 13</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p>&nbsp;</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">We want to do three things here in Chicago. We want to make Chicago an international city. We want to bring headquarters for companies in here. And we want to build Chicago for its people.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Mayor Richard J. Daley, as quoted by A. Robert Abboud, First National Bank of Chicago, President, interview excerpt, December 3, 2009</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em> </em></p>
<div id="attachment_981" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-981 size-medium" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007-300x242.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley operating a piece of construction equipment, ca. 1950s. RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007" width="300" height="242" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007-300x242.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007-1024x827.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007-1080x872.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley operating a piece of construction equipment, ca. 1950s. RJD_04_01_0040_0005_007</p></div>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">I think he did a great job of building the city, turning it into a great city, and interacting with the federal government. It was building the city, getting the expressway systems built, getting O&#8217;Hare built, getting UIC built, and getting so many of the buildings downtown built. I think he did a great job of turning the city into a world class city.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Robert G. Vanecko, grandson of Richard J. Daley, interview excerpt, March 5, 2010</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em> </em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_1 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">2 of 13</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">A city engineer discusses building projects. Click on image to play video.</p>

<!-- iframe plugin v.4.3 wordpress.org/plugins/iframe/ -->
<iframe width="420" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/yT5Ts9b1ARs" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" 0="allowfullscreen" scrolling="yes" class="iframe-class"></iframe>

<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Video: Robert Christensen, Executive Director Public Building Commission, interview excerpt, September 8, 2003</em></p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">He helped hospitals in their plans for expansion and ways to do things. I would only find out about it sometimes because some CEO of a hospital or someone like that would tell me. &#8220;Your father-in-law was very helpful to us, getting these people to come on our board and tell us to go ahead on this.&#8221;</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Dr. Robert M. Vanecko, MD, son-in-law of Richard J. Daley, interview excerpt, March 8, 2010</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em> </em></p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_2 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">3 of 13</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><div id="attachment_961" style="width: 811px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-961 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001-801x1024.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley, Governor William G. Stratton, and unidentified man with shovels at McCormick Place groundbreaking. RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001" width="801" height="1024" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001-801x1024.jpg 801w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001-235x300.jpg 235w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001-1080x1381.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001.jpg 1173w" sizes="(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley, Governor William G. Stratton, and unidentified man with shovels at McCormick Place groundbreaking. RJD_04_01_0014_0003_001</p></div></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_3 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">4 of 13</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p style="text-align: left;">Providing services and programs to Chicagoans was part of a larger plan to revitalize the city&#8217;s downtown &#8220;Loop&#8221; area and strengthen its infrastructure.</p>
<div id="attachment_1112" style="width: 219px" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0029_0008_010.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-1112 size-medium" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0029_0008_010-209x300.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley giving a speech at an outdoor podium in front of the Sears Tower (now known as the Willis Tower), ca. 1970s. RJD_04_01_0029_0008_010" width="209" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0029_0008_010-209x300.jpg 209w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0029_0008_010-712x1024.jpg 712w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0029_0008_010.jpg 1043w" sizes="(max-width: 209px) 100vw, 209px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley giving a speech at an outdoor podium in front of the Sears Tower (now known as the Willis Tower), ca. 1970s. RJD_04_01_0029_0008_010</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">He always believed that if you kept the core of the apple strong, the apple would stay strong. So the downtown, even though he took a lot of heat for protecting the downtown and keeping that strong, and [was] told always he was ignoring the neighborhoods, he thought that if he didn&#8217;t keep that core strong, the Loop, then the apple would turn bad.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>William Daley, son of Richard J. Daley, interview excerpt, January 12, 2009</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em> </em></p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_4 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">5 of 13</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p style="text-align: left;">Both Mayor Richard J. Daley and later his son, Mayor Richard M. Daley (1989-2011) contributed to the city’s built environment.</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">Most of the downtown was developed under his dad. Most of the neighborhoods were developed under Rich. We’re lucky to have the Daleys because I wouldn’t want to be going through a new mayor every four years—things would never get done.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Vince Gavin, Daley Security Chief and Liquor Commissioner, interview excerpt, June 19, 2014</em></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em> </em></p>
</blockquote>
<div id="attachment_975" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-975 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002-1024x848.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley with two unidentified men at the groundbreaking ceremony for the 1000 Lake Shore Plaza building, ca. 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006" width="1024" height="848" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002-1024x848.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002-300x248.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002-1080x894.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley with two unidentified men at the groundbreaking ceremony for the 1000 Lake Shore Plaza building, ca. 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006</p></div></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_5 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">6 of 13</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><div id="attachment_971" style="width: 691px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-971 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006-681x1024.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley with two unidentified men at the groundbreaking ceremony for the 1000 Lake Shore Plaza building, ca. 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006" width="681" height="1024" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006-681x1024.jpg 681w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006-200x300.jpg 200w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006.jpg 998w" sizes="(max-width: 681px) 100vw, 681px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley with two unidentified men at the groundbreaking ceremony for the 1000 Lake Shore Plaza building, ca. 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0007_006</p></div></div>
							
